******
[1] France, increasing cases
Date: 28 Aug 2008
Source: French Ministry of Agriculture's web site [edited]
<http://agriculture.gouv.fr/sections/thematiques/sante-protection-animaux/maladies-animales/fievre-catarrhale-ovine/fichier-telecharger-7/downloadFile/FichierAttache_3_f0/pds_280808.pdf>


Direction generale de l'alimentation, Bureau de Sante Animale has issued on
the French Ministry of Agriculture's website dated 28 Aug 2008 the
following information:

The confirmation of new cases of bluetongue BTV-1 in Aude, Gers, and
Lot-et-Garonne has caused a modification in the zonage of the perimeters.
This zonage was instituted by decree on 27 Aug 2008 and defined the
regulated zones relative to bluetongue. The text is to be published and
will come into force on 28 Aug 2008.

The actual list of regulated communes will only show the communes which
appear in the regulated zone.

8167 cases of bluetongue serotype BTV-8 in the year 2008 came from viral
circulation in 2008. 178 new cases of bluetongue serotype BTV-1 came from
viral circulation in 2008.

15 569 cases of bluetongue were declared in 2007 (3 cases of BTV-1).

6020 cases of bluetongue BTV-8 declared in the 1st 6 months of 2008 came
from viral circulation in 2007 (6 cases of bluetongue serotype BTV-1).

--
